arts intensive program 2009 arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe featured archive gallery arts intensive program 2009 the inaugural arts intensive program which ran for three weeks in september 2009 brought 52 undergraduates together with stanford arts faculty and visiting artist ralph lemon to develop creative projects in film design thinking sound engineering stage design and dance the inaugural arts intensive summer program took place during september 2009 the three week program consisted of 52 undergraduate students in six arts courses of various disciplines during the program students worked full time on creative projects diving into the artistic process and final presentations students worked directly with stanford arts faculty as well as acclaimed visiting artist ralph lemon in workshop and class settings students were grouped by discipline including documentary film design thinking sound engineering stage design and dance each group created a final presentation which was displayed or performed at the end of the program the arts intensive included an inter disciplinary component where students exchanged presentations and attended faculty lectures the students also traveled off the farm on an arts scavenger hunt where they discovered public art around san francisco and attended various galleries exhibitions and performances arts intensive program website lili hsu home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
